# OncoBridge Intelligence — Coolify Environment Variables
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# This file documents every environment variable the app needs.
# It is safe to commit — it contains NO real credentials.
#
# HOW TO USE:
#   Coolify → Application → Environment Variables → Add each key below
#   Mark NEO4J_PASSWORD, OPENAI_API_KEY, GEMINI_API_KEY, ADMIN_PASSWORD as Secret
#
# LOCAL DEV:
#   Copy to .env at project root and fill in real values.
#   .env is gitignored — never commit it.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# ── Neo4j AuraDB (Knowledge Graph) ───────────────────────────────────────────
NEO4J_URI=neo4j+s://YOUR_INSTANCE.databases.neo4j.io
NEO4J_USERNAME=neo4j
NEO4J_PASSWORD=your-auradb-password-here

# ── LLM APIs ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# GPT-4o primary — set this to enable AI Research Assistant
OPENAI_API_KEY=sk-proj-...

# Gemini Flash fallback — used if OPENAI_API_KEY is not set
GEMINI_API_KEY=AIza...

# ── Admin Panel ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Password for the hidden /admin_logs page (99_admin_logs.py)
# Must be a non-empty string — an empty value blocks all access
ADMIN_PASSWORD=choose-a-strong-password-here

# ── Optional ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# NCBI API key raises PubMed rate limit from 3 → 10 requests/sec
# Leave blank if not needed
NCBI_API_KEY=

# GitHub Gist visitor log (used by admin page)
# Set these only if you want visitor analytics via GitHub Gist backend
GITHUB_GIST_TOKEN=
GITHUB_GIST_ID=

# ── Docker DNS (important for Neo4j AuraDB connectivity) ─────────────────────
# If deploying with Docker run directly, add: --dns 8.8.8.8 --dns 8.8.4.4
# In Coolify, set DNS via the service "Advanced" → "Docker run options" field:
#   --dns 8.8.8.8 --dns 8.8.4.4
# This ensures the container can resolve external hostnames like databases.neo4j.io
